First of All: Download their app. You get $5 off and when you spend $100 you get $10 credit.  Pretty awesome. (You can also use up whatever you have on your paper punch card ($1 off per hole)). Just to go the app store, and they have both Android and iOS. The app will be linked to your credit card, and you can just pay with a QR code instead of your credit card. It's convenient and a receipt is emailed to you.  This place is right by my office and it is THE lunch spot. Don't even try to get there at noon. The line is long. I've never actually waited before, so not sure how quickly it moves. I only go here around 11:00-11:30 when the line is short. I've tried going multiple times at 1pm, but I guess most people eat late, so the line was still pretty long.  The food is good. It's a good healthy option is that's what you're feeling like for lunch. I have not tried their sandwiches or salads, and I've done their large takeout box twice. The small takeout just comes with one scoop whereas the large comes with two scoops. And you get a meat/protein and then some type of rice, and two sides. There is also lots of vegetarian option. The first time, I tried their meatballs, which I really enjoyed and then I also tried their grilled chicken. I thought for healthier options, they did a good job preparing these meat options. I've had their Brussels sprouts, kale, cauliflower with chickpeas. I thought some of the veggies were overcooked and too soggy for me. Hence, I removed a star.  I was really impressed by the staff. They were really patient my very first time there. They handed me a menu and explained what to expect. They also gave me a free drink for being a first timer! They were really great. It was very empty then, so you might not always get that attention depending on when you go!

Dig Inn makes you want to dig in! This is a very popular lunch spot around FiDi. It serves really fresh and delicious lunch options.  Basically, you pick a lunch box (small or large) and one protein, 1 main carb and 3 side dishes for a fixed price. Today is my first visit and I opted for their organic tofu salad as my protein source and it is very good. For carb, I got the brown rice although they also have veggie rice and green as options. For side dishes, I really like the kale and apple salad and quinoa & roasted butternut squash.  Everything tastes really fresh, light and well made. I would like to try their heavier option of protein such as braised beef. It looked damn good in the tray! My small tofu salad box is $8 with tax and it is not too bad. If you are REALLY hungry, I suggest you go with the big box.
It's healthy, it's delicious, but the serving sizes are too small. I prefer a salad somewhere else over this business. The peanut butter shakes are all water.
The kale apple salad made my Wednesday. So did the meatballs. So did the roasted beets. So did their rewards card program. So did...

I really like how you can get a ton of healthy options (especially vegetarian) without it just being your typical salad, and I really like the combinations they have each day that all seem pretty new and interesting. If you grab the bigger box, you're getting a ton of food that can last you at least a meal and a half. It's pretty cheap when you think about how much food you're getting and it compares well to the other stuff in this area. The only comment I have is with the other commenters here that the food itself is quite bland and could do better with nothing more than a little seasoning or hot sauce.
